nd recast/effect time , or 583/250/2.33/4.5/0 in a shortened form.)<br>Celestial Cleansing is 700/225/3.11/1.5/30<br><br>CC is superior in: Total HP healed, healing Efficiency and casting time, and is balanced by its recast/heal-over-time effect time nature.<br><br>SH has no stacking issues, and takes effect immediately.<br><br>CC is ~33% more mana efficient than Superior Healing.<br><br>Let us now consider a level 60 Paladin with Spell Casting Reinforcement 3, Healing Gift 3, and Healing Adept 3, and look at the numbers again. (Averaging in the critical heals at the advertised rate of 10%, and averaging in the 20% occuring 6th tick of CC)<br><br>Superior Healing: 705/250/2.82/4.5/0<br>Celestial Cleansing: 910/225/4.04/1.5/30<br><br>CC is then ~43% more mana efficient than Superior Healing. A slight decrease in relative efficiency, but one must consider that there are two skills (HA and HG) augmenting Superior Healing, while only one (SCR) for CC.<br><br>Let us now fast forward to a level 65 Paladin with his new spells and AA abilities, and compare the instant heal and heal-over-time spells he would be using.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Divine Light vs Supernal Cleansing</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (at Level 60)<br><br>Divine Light is 910/350/2.6/4.5/0<br>Supernal Cleansing is 900/300/3.0/1.5/30<br><br>This is the baseline - no AA's whatsoever.<br><br>SC is superior to DL once again in efficiency and casting time, but no longer heals more than the comparable direct heal.<br><br>SC in this case is only 15% more mana efficient than Divine Light<br><br>Now let's factor in all of the healing AA's, Luclin and POP. (SCR; HA; HG; Adv. HA - an additional 15%; Adv. HG - an additional 6%)<br><br>Divine Light: 1319/350/3.77/4.5/0<br>Supernal Cleansing: 1170/300/3.90/1.5/0<br><br>Divine Light still heals more, and now Supernal Cleansing is only ~3% more efficient than Divine Light.<br><br>It has already been well noted on these forums that Supernal Cleansing is also less efficient than Celestial Cleansing. It is, as far as I'm aware, unprecedented for a higher level heal in the same line to be less efficient than its predecessor.<br><br>But also, as we progress in levels and AA's, our line of combat heals, which doesn't stack and has a 30 second recast drops in efficiency relative to our best comparable direct heal - from 43% to 3%.<br><br>This to me is further evidence that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     Supernal Cleansing should be upgraded to heal 250HP/tick</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. This would help remove two discrepancies:<br><br>1. It would change the baseline SC ratio to 3.33, an improvement over CC's 3.11.<br><br>2. It would change the aforementioned &quot;4 levels&quot; of relative efficiency between the HOT and direct heals from (33% -&gt; 43% -&gt; 15% -&gt;  3%) to (33% -&gt; 43% -&gt; 28% -&gt; 15%), a much more reasonable progression.<br><br>Edit: Made two math errors, corrected.<br><br><br>For Reference:<br><br>Supernal Cleansing - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3485&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>Divine Light - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1519&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>Celestial Cleansing - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1283&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>Superior Healing - <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=9&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulolahoss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lola Hoss</A> at: 10/1/02 11:16:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td no